"""
NeuralFoil Aerodynamic Simulation Module — v3 (Corrected)
==========================================================
Evaluates all bird-inspired airfoils across a comprehensive flight-condition
matrix and extracts category-level performance champions.

Changes from v2
----------------
1.  DRAG CORRECTION (§1)
    NeuralFoil systematically under-predicts drag at low Re. A Re-dependent
    correction factor, calibrated against published XFOIL / wind-tunnel data
    for NACA 0012 / 2412 / 4412 airfoils, is applied to every CD value
    before L/D is computed.  Corrections are largest at Re = 1e4 (~+60 %)
    and taper to near-zero at Re ≥ 5e5.

2.  IMPROVED STALL DETECTION (§2)
    The v2 algorithm used a flat 5 %-of-CLmax threshold, which failed on
    NeuralFoil's smooth CL curves and reported stall at 20° for nearly
    every airfoil.  The new algorithm combines:
      a) dCL/dα slope monitoring (stall when slope drops below 40 % of
         the linear-region slope),
      b) a curvature (d²CL/dα²) sign-change check, and
      c) the original peak-drop method as a fallback.
    The stall angle is the *earliest* trigger among these three.

3.  PLAUSIBILITY FILTERING (§3)
    Physical plausibility bounds reject individual (α, Re) data-points
    whose values fall outside published envelopes:
      • L/D ≤ 80   (even high-performance sailplanes rarely exceed this)
      • CD  ≥ 0.004 (skin-friction floor for turbulent boundary layers)
      • |CL| ≤ 2.2  (realistic single-element airfoil limit)
    Implausible points are flagged and excluded from summary statistics.

4.  REYNOLDS ESTIMATION (§4)
    The heuristic velocity model is replaced by an allometric scaling law
    from Pennycuick (2008) and Hedenström & Alerstam (1995):
        V_mp ≈ 4.09 · m^{0.21}              (minimum-power speed, m in kg)
    combined with a chord estimate from wingspan allometry.  When body
    mass is not available, the v2 heuristic is retained but flagged.

5.  EXPANDED VALIDATION (§5)
    The NACA benchmark suite now includes error-distribution metrics
    (MAE, RMSE, bias) across all test conditions, and the validation
    results are persisted as a structured CSV.

6.  ADDITIONAL PERFORMANCE METRICS (§6)
      • Endurance parameter:  CL^{1.5} / CD  (maximise for loiter)
      • Pitching-moment stability:  dCM/dCL slope
      • Drag-bucket width:  Δα over which CD < 1.1 × CD_min
      • Range parameter:  CL / CD  (same as L/D, retained for clarity)

7.  GEOMETRY–PERFORMANCE STATISTICS (§7)
    Pearson and Spearman correlations between geometric descriptors
    (t/c, max camber, camber location) and performance metrics are
    computed per category and globally, and exported as a CSV.

References
----------
Drela, M. (1989). XFOIL: An analysis and design system for low Reynolds
    number airfoils. *Low Reynolds Number Aerodynamics*, Springer.
Pennycuick, C. J. (2008). *Modelling the Flying Bird*. Elsevier.
Hedenström, A. & Alerstam, T. (1995). Optimal flight speed of birds.
    *Phil. Trans. R. Soc. B*, 348(1326), 471–487.
NeuralFoil documentation: github.com/peterdsharpe/NeuralFoil
"""

